thread.title: HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP: B-R football falls to unbeaten Marshfield

author: Staff Reports
title: HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP: B-R football falls to unbeaten Marshfield
text: HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP: B-R football falls to unbeaten Marshfield Norton boys soccer remains undefeated through nine games By Staff Reports The Taunton Daily Gazette, Taunton, MA By Staff Reports Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 11:01 PM Updated at 11:11 PM Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 11:01 PM Updated at 11:11 PM BRIDGEWATER — The Bridgewater-Raynham football team came up a little bit short against undefeated Marshfield on Friday The Rams collected three return touchdowns, including two from interception returns for scores by Danny Dalton and Adam McNamara as Marshfield tops the Trojans 40-28 at Bridgewater-Raynham Regional High School. Brendan Ward also had an 85-yard kickoff return for a touchdown for the Rams. Shawn Noel Jr., Bryce Shaw, Cade McNaughton and Steve D'Emilia scored touchdowns for B-R (1-3). D'Emila also threw two touchdown passes. The Trojans travel to Dartmouth next week Attleboro 41 The Tigers (0-4) dropped their fourth straight of the season, losing to league opponent Attleboro. Taunton is at Mansfield next week. Millis 34 The Lancers (2-2) drops a home game to league opponent Millis. Norton travels to Bellingham next week. GIRLS SOCCER Westwood 3 The Lancers (3-4-3) defeated league opponent Westwood. Shelly Belcher had three goals for Norton in the win. Julia Palin also scored a goal. The Lancers are at Bellingham Tuesday. BOYS SOCCER Westwood 1 The Lancers (8-0-1) remain unbeaten after beating league opponent Westwood. Jordan Lach scored the winning goal for Norton with eight minutes remaining on an assists from Jared Kahn. Jon Lach also scored on a penalty kick. Ryan Blakeley had four saves in net. The Lancers host Bellingham Tuesday. GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Taunton 3 Mansfield 2 The Tigers (7-3; 6-2 in Hockomock League) won three of five matches — 11-25, 29-27,25-20, 16-25 and 15-12 — against league opponent Mansfield. Tatum Speicher led the way for Taunton with 39 assists, six digs and three kill shots. Molly Sullivan chipped in with 16 digs. Meghan Navarro had 15 digs and three aces. Kelsey Hebert finished with four digs, an ace and was perfect from the line. Dighton-Rehoboth 3 Apponequet 0 The Falcons swept three straight games — 25-20 25-17 and 25-19 — from league opponent Apponequet. Lucia Maslen led the way for D-R with 11 digs and four aces. Kylie D'Ambrosio chipped in with four aces and six assists. Jenai Child finished with two blocks, two aces and two kill shots. The Falcons are at Case Monday. Bridgewater-Raynham 3 Fontbonne 0 The Trojans (5-4) defeated non-league opponent Fontbonne in three straight games — 25-13, 25-21 and 25-22. Natalie Sorrenti, Ashley Rose, Megan Shaughnessy, Sophia Falconeiri and Mikayla Morrill played well for B-R in the victory. Holliston 3 Norton 1 The Lancers (3-6) dropped three of four games — 23-25, 25-21, 22-25 and 15-25 — to league opponent Holliston. Page 2 of 2 - Casey Holmes led the way for Norton with four blocks, four kill shots and eight aces. Sarah Lavoie chipped in with four aces and four assists. Leah Buttner finished with four kill shots and four aces. The Lancers host Westwood Wednesday. By Staff Reports The Taunton Daily Gazette, Taunton, MA By Staff Reports Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 11:01 PM Updated at 11:11 PM
